The paper deals with the hardness of approximation for graph problems, specifically Label Cover and the basic k-spanner problem. This suggests that it could belong to categories related to computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses on graph problems and their approximations, categories related to graph theory (cs.GT) and combinatorics (cs.DM) could also be possible.
